fields.name:<:think:585665071938666508> Should You Use Ubuntu Budgie?;
fields.value:If you like stock Ubuntu, but it isn't quite customizable enough for you, Ubuntu Budgie may be the distribution for you.
**[Download Ubuntu Budgie](http://cdimage.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-budgie/releases/18.04.2/release/)**

If you'd like something even lighter on system resources than Ubuntu Budgie, we recommend checking out Xubuntu (see `sudo info xubuntu`), Ubuntu MATE (see `sudo info ubuntu mate`), or KDE neon (see `sudo info KDE neon`).}}